author: Fraudulein
text:
Â @Just a Cat with a Sad FaceÂ  What? That's not at all what I said.
(In fact the artist that drew a doujinshi based on a particular franchise will probably use at least some of the profits to buy merch of that franchise, so you could argue that buying the doujinshi does indirectly support the original franchise, not to mention derivative works help keep a fandom alive)

What doesn't support the franchise nor the doujin artists, is people reading the doujins for free on some site that hosts a bunch of unauthorized scans, which in worst cases even include the page that says not to upload the contents online, fully translated.
